                        <p>15th century, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName> (as MS.): wood boards with inside bevel, rounded corners; brown leather, 
                           blind-tooled with lines, stamps and strapwork to form on each cover a panel around a large strapwork cross on a base (very worn); spine plain; 
                           single central clasp, extant, with a strap of thick tawed? leather and brass tip, running to a flat trefoil-shaped brass catch-plate on lower cover; 
